            <h1>Embedded Systems</h1>
            <p>Explore the fascinating world of hardware-software integration that powers smart devices and IoT solutions</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- About Section -->
    <section class="section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">What are Embedded Systems?</h2>
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Embedded systems are specialized computing systems designed to perform dedicated functions within larger mechanical or electrical systems. Unlike general-purpose computers, embedded systems are optimized for specific tasks, combining hardware and software components to create efficient, reliable, and often real-time solutions.</p>
                    <p>As an embedded systems engineer, you'll work at the intersection of hardware and software, designing and implementing systems that control everything from household appliances and medical devices to industrial automation equipment and automotive electronics. You'll need to understand both the physical constraints of hardware and the logical flow of software to create integrated solutions.</p>
                    <p>This field is experiencing rapid growth with the proliferation of Internet of Things (IoT) devices, smart appliances, wearable technology, and autonomous systems. Embedded systems engineers are in high demand across various industries, making this a rewarding specialization within electrical engineering.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="image-content">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517420704952-d9f39e95b43e?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Embedded Systems">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Areas Section -->
    <section class="section bg-dark" id="key-areas">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Key Areas of Study</h2>
            <p class="section-intro">Embedded Systems encompasses several specialized areas that form the foundation of modern smart devices and control systems:</p>
            
            <div class="cards-grid three-columns">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-microchip"></i> Microcontroller Architecture</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of microcontroller internals, including CPU cores, memory systems, peripherals, and instruction sets that form the hardware foundation of embedded systems.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">CPU Architectures</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">ARM, RISC-V, PIC, AVR architectures and instruction sets</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Memory Systems</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Flash, RAM, EEPROM, memory management units</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Peripherals</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Timers, ADCs, DACs, communication interfaces</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-code"></i> Embedded Software</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The development of software specifically for embedded devices, focusing on resource constraints, reliability, and real-time performance requirements.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Firmware Development</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Bare-metal programming, bootloaders, device drivers</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Programming Languages</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">C, C++, Assembly, Rust for embedded systems</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Software Architecture</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">State machines, event-driven programming, layered design</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Real-Time Systems</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The design and implementation of systems with strict timing constraints, where operations must complete within guaranteed deadlines to ensure correct functionality.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">RTOS Fundamentals</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Task scheduling, synchronization, resource management</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Real-Time Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Deadline analysis, priority inversion, jitter control</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">RTOS Implementations</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">FreeRTOS, Zephyr, RT-Linux, VxWorks</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cards-grid three-columns" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-network-wired"></i> Communication Protocols</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The standards and methods used for data exchange between embedded systems and other devices, including wired and wireless protocols for various applications.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Wired Protocols</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">I2C, SPI, UART, CAN, Ethernet, USB</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Wireless Protocols</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Bluetooth, WiFi, ZigBee, LoRa, NB-IoT</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Protocol Implementation</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Driver development, stack integration, debugging</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-bolt"></i> Power Management</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>Techniques and strategies for optimizing energy consumption in embedded systems, critical for battery-powered and energy-efficient devices.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Low-Power Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Sleep modes, clock gating, voltage scaling</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Battery Management</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Charging circuits, fuel gauging, protection</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Energy Harvesting</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Solar, thermal, vibration, RF energy sources</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Security & Safety</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>Protecting embedded systems from unauthorized access and ensuring they operate safely, especially important for critical infrastructure and safety-critical applications.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Embedded Security</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Secure boot, encryption, authentication, secure storage</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Safety Standards</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">IEC 61508, ISO 26262, DO-178C compliance</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Secure Development</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Threat modeling, secure coding, vulnerability testing</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

